				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">New Bard seeking help - Skills seem to have Stopped<a name="47327"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jun 21 04 11:48 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Greetings all,
<br />

<br />
My very first EQ creation and now my all-time favorite is my Bard. I am still learning to play the many roles a bard can perform, thanks a lot to the guides and forums on this board. 
<br />

<br />
But for some reason my skill advancement seems to have stalled out at level 37. For 2 levels &quot;Detect Traps&quot; has NOT moved, and I trigger it after EVERY song. It is at 116.
<br />

<br />
Defense has slowed to  a snails pace at 181 and weapons skills are also VERY slow. After almost a full yellow of exp fighting low blues I have 1 weapon skill up and 1 defense. Previously I could have expected defense at 3/4 and my primary weapon maxed. Previous levels were slow but NOT this slow. Offense is the only skill going up, and it is maxed for this level already!
<br />

<br />
Song skills are also very slow, taking upwards of 3-4 hours just sitting and singing to get 5 skill ups. Bind wounds has also stopped at 150 (I believe the max is 200). I tend to get a lot of bind wound practice as I work on Melee skills (attack until at 30%, mez mob, bind wounds to 70%, repeat ...).
<br />

<br />
The slow down seems to have happened after last Tuesday's path but that is probably a coincidence.
<br />

<br />
My Dex hovers at around 135, in combat is 156. Dex is a factor in Song and weapon skill ups right? Agility is at 157 when I am in combat, I think AGI helps defense. My INT is only about 83, is this a factor for Bards?
<br />

<br />
I have previously been able to max out all skills (besides hand-to-hand) at each level. I tend to melee until weapons/defense/offence/etc. are maxed, AFK sing at night and during work, and gain exp via charm or AOE kiting depending on the mob (I look forward to swarm kite when my charm improves). I really work hard on Defense, it has proven very nice to have when a kite goes wrong or a mob  warp happens! 
<br />

<br />
Any thoughs, suggestions or comments would be greatly appreciated. Or perhaps there is a guide posted that I missed that explains this?
<br />

<br />
</span></td>
